      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental hemolysis index comparison — FDA generic centrifugal pump",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against in-vitro measurements from three independent laboratories. Mean relative error across 5 operating points: 8.3%. RH < 1 satisfied at all worst-case conditions. Turbulence model sensitivity study (k-omega SST vs. RSM) showed < 5% variation in NIH predictions."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cpb-mesh-vr-002",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (3.2 M, 8.7 M, 22.1 M elements) conducted at the highest-shear operating point. GCI-based discretization uncertainty estimated at 4.1% for NIH. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Grid convergence index < 5% on fine mesh."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cpb-sqa-vr-003",
