      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "NIH directly maps to the clinical hemolysis endpoint; QoI relevance confirmed by domain expert review.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis is the accepted surrogate for pump-induced red cell damage and is the regulatory quantity used in 510(k) submissions for CPB devices. QoI relevance confirmed by clinical advisory review. Requirement met."
    },
